                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="225194" author="pjones" created="Thu, 5 Apr 2018 13:19:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ben&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You should be setup to be able to re-trigger tests now&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="216891" author="bevans" created="Wed, 20 Dec 2017 21:00:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;From a non-priviliged user&apos;s perspective, if I push a commit to gerrit, and provisioning fails, my only recourse to try again is to either rebase the change (if possible) or make a silly change, like adding a space or a period to the commit message and pushing it again.  There&apos;s no way for me to hit a &quot;try it again&quot; button.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These don&apos;t happen often, but they do seem to come in bursts, and it gets pretty frustrating.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="216889" author="jamesanunez" created="Wed, 20 Dec 2017 20:48:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ben - When node-provisioning fails, autotest does try several times to load/configure Lustre on the nodes. The issue I&apos;ve run into is that the node or VM may be bad and it would be beneficial for the initialization to be retried on a different set of nodes/VMs. Retrying on different nodes/VMs was requested previously and remains an open issue. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
